                </div>
                <div class="right">
                 <h3>
                  <a href="/news/2018-kyoko-selden-memorial-translation-prize-japanese-literature-thought-and-society">
                   2018 Kyoko Selden Memorial Translation Prize in Japanese Literature, Thought, and Society
                  </a>
                 </h3>
                 The Department of Asian Studies at Cornell University is pleased to announce the 2018 prize honoring the life and work of our colleague, Kyoko Selden. The prize pays homage to the finest achievements in Japanese literature, thought, and society through the medium of translation. The “Already Published Translator” prize has been awarded to Dawn Lawson for Nakajima Shōen’s A Famous Flower in Mountain Seclusion (Sankan no meika, 1889). The “Unpublished Translator” prize has been awarded to Max Zimmerman for translating the short story “An Artificial Heart” (Jinkō Shinzō, 1926) by Kosakai Fuboku.
                </div>
               </span>
              </div>
